26:44.020 --> 26:45.280
DAMN IT, LET --

26:45.290 --> 26:47.080
HI.

26:47.090 --> 26:48.350
HI.

26:48.350 --> 26:50.180
WHY DID YOU SAY
THOSE THINGS TO ME?

26:52.490 --> 26:55.680
WHAT THINGS?
THE THINGS THE OTHER DAY.

26:55.690 --> 26:57.020
WHAT DID I SAY?

26:57.020 --> 27:00.220
DON'T EVER
TALK TO ME AGAIN.

27:00.220 --> 27:01.680
OKAY.

27:01.690 --> 27:03.750
AND STOP LOOKING
IN MY WINDOW.

27:07.020 --> 27:09.620
BUT YOU'RE SO BEAUTIFUL.

27:09.620 --> 27:11.280
I'LL CALL THE POLICE.

27:11.290 --> 27:13.420
YEAH, WELL, YOU MIGHT WANT
TO CALL THEM.

27:13.420 --> 27:15.120
I'LL TELL MY HUSBAND.

27:17.550 --> 27:21.520
YOU KNOW,
NO ONE BELIEVES YOU, RIGHT?

27:21.520 --> 27:22.780
YES, HE DOES.

27:22.790 --> 27:26.020
NO, NO, NO, HE --
HE THINKS YOU'RE CRAZY.

27:26.020 --> 27:28.380
I AM NOT CRAZY.
NO?

27:28.390 --> 27:29.780
WELL,
HE THINKS YOU ARE.

27:29.790 --> 27:31.420
MY HUSBAND DOES NOT
THINK I'M CRAZY.

27:31.420 --> 27:32.780
REALLY?

27:32.790 --> 27:37.020
WELL, THEN WHY DID HE COME OVER
HERE AND TELL ME THAT YOU WERE?

27:37.020 --> 27:40.080
YOU'RE A HORRIBLE MAN
AND YOU'RE A LIAR.

27:40.090 --> 27:42.350
JUST DON'T EVER TALK
TO ME AGAIN!

27:42.350 --> 27:44.280
YOU DO KNOW THAT YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO CAME OVER HERE

27:44.290 --> 27:46.620
AND KNOCKED
ON<i> MY</i> DOOR, RIGHT?

27:46.620 --> 27:48.750
YES, I DID.
OKAY.

27:48.750 --> 27:52.080
WELL, DON'T BRING YOUR ASS
OVER TO MY HOUSE ANYMORE

27:52.090 --> 27:53.750
AND, UH,
I WON'T TALK TO YOU.

27:53.750 --> 27:56.380
WELL,
DON'T LOOK AT ME NAKED.

27:56.390 --> 27:59.020
DID YOU ENJOY
LOOKING AT ME NAKED?

28:01.250 --> 28:04.680
YOU'RE A SAD
LITTLE MAN.

28:04.690 --> 28:06.220
LITTLE?
NO, NO.

28:06.220 --> 28:09.550
CLEARLY YOU DIDN'T GET
A GOOD ENOUGH LOOK.

28:09.550 --> 28:11.880
WANT TO TRY AGAIN?
HUH?

28:11.890 --> 28:13.480
YOU SURE?
YOU SURE?

28:13.490 --> 28:14.550
NO.
DON'T BE AFRAID OF IT.

28:14.550 --> 28:15.820
NO.

28:15.820 --> 28:16.880
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
I'LL SEE YOU NEXT TIME.

28:16.890 --> 28:18.020
-HEY, HEY.
-HI.

28:18.020 --> 28:19.920
HI. HOW ARE YOU?

28:19.920 --> 28:21.680
I'M FINE.

28:23.450 --> 28:25.080
IS HE BOTHERING YOU?

28:25.090 --> 28:26.350
UM, YEAH.

28:26.350 --> 28:28.420
HE'S BEEN LOOKING
IN MY WINDOW.

28:28.420 --> 28:30.750
I'M SO SORRY.

28:30.750 --> 28:32.950
LOOK, M-MAYBE YOU SHOULD
CLOSE YOUR CURTAINS.

28:32.950 --> 28:34.420
NO.
NO.

28:34.420 --> 28:37.020
UM, I NEED THE LIGHT.
IT HELPS ME THINK.

28:37.020 --> 28:38.350
MM.

28:38.350 --> 28:40.350
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU
CALL THE POLICE.

28:40.350 --> 28:43.220
NO.

28:43.220 --> 28:44.880
HE WON'T STOP.

28:44.890 --> 28:46.980
HE BETTER STOP.

28:49.390 --> 28:50.580
DID YOU TELL
YOUR HUSBAND?

28:50.590 --> 28:52.720
NO.
UM, HE...

28:52.720 --> 28:54.220
I CAN'T.
WHAT?

28:54.220 --> 28:57.820
HE ALREADY HAS ENOUGH
ON HIS PLATE.

28:57.820 --> 29:00.820
OH, WELL, YOU NEED
TO TELL SOMEBODY.

29:00.820 --> 29:03.020
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

29:03.020 --> 29:04.450
OKAY.

29:04.450 --> 29:06.050
SWEET ROLLS?

29:06.050 --> 29:07.250
OH, YEAH.

29:07.250 --> 29:08.850
I'M GOING IN TO COOK.

29:08.850 --> 29:13.220
IF YOU ADD A LITTLE CINNAMON,
IT MAKES THEM TASTE GREAT.

29:13.220 --> 29:14.850
OKAY.
I WILL.

29:14.850 --> 29:17.580
OKAY.

29:17.590 --> 29:21.120
THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME
THE OTHER NIGHT.

29:21.120 --> 29:23.020
SURE.

29:23.020 --> 29:26.420
I'M SURE MY HUSBAND TOLD YOU
ABOUT MY CONDITION.

29:26.420 --> 29:27.680
YES.

29:27.690 --> 29:30.620
IT DOESN'T HAPPEN UNLESS
I DON'T TAKE MY MEDS, SO...

29:30.620 --> 29:31.820
I UNDERSTAND.

29:31.820 --> 29:33.750
OKAY.

29:33.750 --> 29:34.750
UM, THANKS AGAIN.

29:34.750 --> 29:36.920
SURE.

29:36.920 --> 29:46.350
♪♪

29:46.350 --> 29:47.750
BYE, TRASH.

29:47.750 --> 29:50.850
I'M-A TELL LUSHION
WHEN HE GETS HOME, TOO.

29:50.850 --> 29:52.450
TELL HIS ASS.
TELL LUSHION.

29:52.450 --> 29:54.220
MM-HMM.
I'M-A TELL LUSHION.

29:54.220 --> 29:57.180
ALL RIGHT.
SON OF A BITCH.

29:57.190 --> 29:58.980
PLEASE LET HIM KNOW,
OKAY?

29:58.990 --> 30:00.620
AND WHERE IS YOUR CAR?

30:00.620 --> 30:02.620
DID YOU WALK
TO THE GROCERY STORE?

30:02.620 --> 30:03.680
IT'S LIKE A MILE.

30:03.690 --> 30:05.950
WHO WALKS
TO THE GROCERY STORE?

30:05.950 --> 30:07.620
WE DON'T DO THAT
IN THIS NEIGHBORHOOD.

30:07.620 --> 30:10.620
WE AIN'T GOT NO CORNER STORE,
NO LIQUOR STORE, NO, UH --

30:10.620 --> 30:12.350
NO CHECK-CASHING PLACE.

30:12.350 --> 30:14.280
CAN'T GET FRIED CHICKEN
ON THE CORNER

30:14.290 --> 30:17.080
AND NO PLACE
TO GET YOUR WEAVE DONE!

30:19.820 --> 30:21.880
WELCOME TO
THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

30:21.890 --> 30:27.650
♪♪

30:31.090 --> 30:32.950
WHO'S THAT?

30:32.950 --> 30:37.080
YOUR WORST NIGHTMARE.
HUH.

30:37.090 --> 30:39.150
AH.

30:39.150 --> 30:41.420
MORE LIKE
MY SWEETEST DREAM.

30:41.420 --> 30:43.620
COME ON IN,
OFFICER WILLIS.

30:43.620 --> 30:45.820
I'M SURE YOU'VE BEEN
A LOT OF MEN'S SWEETEST DREAM,

30:45.820 --> 30:48.950
BUT I'M NOT THE ONE.

30:48.950 --> 30:52.880
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU TODAY,
OFFICER?

30:52.890 --> 30:55.120
WAS THIS YOUR PLAN?

30:55.120 --> 30:56.520
I'M SORRY.

30:56.520 --> 31:00.480
YOU DIDN'T GET WITH ESPERANZA
AND TRY TO TAKE ME DOWN?

31:00.490 --> 31:03.680
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

31:03.690 --> 31:05.550
THAT'S CUTE.

31:05.550 --> 31:08.080
YOU KNOW HOW MANY PEOPLE
HAVE TRIED TO TAKE ME DOWN?

31:08.090 --> 31:10.980
QUITE A FEW I WOULD IMAGINE.

31:10.990 --> 31:12.080
YOU'D BE RIGHT ABOUT THAT.

31:12.090 --> 31:14.080
MM-HMM.
LET'S SEE.

31:14.090 --> 31:16.350
QUITE A FEW
OF YOUR FELLOW OFFICERS.

31:16.350 --> 31:17.420
MM-HMM.

31:17.420 --> 31:18.550
UH-HUH,
AND SOME OF THE ROOKIES.

31:18.550 --> 31:20.680
ALL HAVE TRIED
AND FAILED.

31:20.690 --> 31:23.550
AND FAILED MISERABLY.
MM-HMM.

31:23.550 --> 31:25.820
WELL, LET ME ASK YOU A QUESTION.
LET ME ASK YOU A QUESTION.

31:25.820 --> 31:28.650
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T COME
BY EARLIER?

31:28.650 --> 31:29.850
I'M NOT INTO
YOUR FRUITY ASS.

31:29.850 --> 31:31.580
HOW MANY TIMES
I GOT TO TELL YOU?

31:31.590 --> 31:33.380
OH, RIGHT.

31:33.390 --> 31:35.420
BUT YOU ARE
INTO JOEY, RIGHT?

31:37.590 --> 31:40.180
WHO THE HELL'S JOEY?

31:40.190 --> 31:42.920
OH, WELL, NATALIE'S SON.

31:42.920 --> 31:44.720
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THAT KID.

31:44.720 --> 31:46.020
NO?
NO.

31:46.020 --> 31:47.750
WELL,
WHAT IF I TOLD YOU

31:47.750 --> 31:50.150
I HAD A FEW OF OUR
MUTUAL FRIENDS HERE EARLIER?

31:50.150 --> 31:53.480
HOW MANY TIMES I GOT TO TELL YOU
WE DON'T HAVE MUTUAL FRIENDS?

31:53.490 --> 31:54.480
MM.

31:54.490 --> 31:55.750
LET'S SEE.

31:55.750 --> 31:57.780
HOW 'BOUT PETE?

31:57.790 --> 31:59.720
I KNOW YOU KNOW JOEY.

31:59.720 --> 32:01.580
ANDREW?

32:05.250 --> 32:08.420
AND HOW THE HELL
WOULD THEY BE HERE?

32:08.420 --> 32:11.750
WHY, GIVING TESTIMONY
AGAINST YOU, MY FRIEND.

32:11.750 --> 32:14.020
AND LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING.

32:14.020 --> 32:17.050
WHEN I'M DONE BUILDING
THIS CASE AGAINST YOU

32:17.050 --> 32:19.250
AND HANDING IT INTO
THE D.A.'S OFFICE,

32:19.250 --> 32:21.720
YOU WON'T NEED TO BE
WORRIED ABOUT ME.

32:21.720 --> 32:23.580
YOU WILL NEED TO WORRY
ABOUT A GANG OF GUYS

32:23.590 --> 32:26.480
LIKE ME DOING FAR WORSE.

32:29.190 --> 32:31.320
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN HAVING FUN
DOING THIS LITTLE GAME,

32:31.320 --> 32:34.180
BUT LET ME
TELL YOU THIS --

32:34.190 --> 32:37.550
NOW'S THE TIME FOR YOU TO STOP
BEFORE THIS GETS EXTREMELY UGLY.

32:37.550 --> 32:40.420
OOH.

32:40.420 --> 32:42.150
IT'S TOO LATE FOR THAT,
MY FRIEND.

32:42.150 --> 32:43.480
HMM.

32:43.490 --> 32:46.020
WELL, IF I HAVE
NOTHING TO LOSE,

32:46.020 --> 32:47.750
I MIGHT AS WELL TAKE YOU
OUT ALREADY, THEN, HUH?

32:47.750 --> 32:52.050
YEAH, WELL,
NOT IF I GET TO YOU FIRST.

32:53.390 --> 32:56.380
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT,
WON'T WE?

32:56.390 --> 32:58.250
I GUESS WE SHALL.

32:58.250 --> 33:00.050
HEY, WHERE'D YOU SAY
ANDREW WAS, BY THE WAY?

33:00.050 --> 33:01.050
IF HE SHOWED UP.

33:01.050 --> 33:05.320
OH, WELL,
PROTECTIVE CUSTODY, BABY.

33:05.320 --> 33:08.850
YOU DIDN'T KNOW?

33:08.850 --> 33:12.420
BUILD YOUR CASE, LAR.

33:12.420 --> 33:14.650
MM.
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

33:14.650 --> 33:17.320
I LOOK FORWARD TO IT.

33:21.020 --> 33:24.420
MM! YOU KNOW YOU GOT AN ASS
LIKE A BLACK GIRL?

33:24.420 --> 33:26.280
MM-MM.

33:26.290 --> 33:27.280
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:31.820 --> 33:33.950
HI.
HEY. I BROUGHT WINE.

33:33.950 --> 33:35.150
COME ON IN.
THANK YOU.

33:35.150 --> 33:36.350
YOU'RE WELCOME.
THANK YOU, THANK YOU.

33:36.350 --> 33:38.550
WOW.

33:38.550 --> 33:40.480
HEY.
HEY.

33:40.490 --> 33:42.620
THANKS FOR COMING.
NOT A PROBLEM.

33:42.620 --> 33:44.080
Y'ALL GO AHEAD AND TALK.

33:44.090 --> 33:46.620
I'M GONNA
CHECK ON THE ROAST.

33:46.620 --> 33:48.280
SURE SMELLS DELICIOUS,
NATALIE.

33:48.290 --> 33:51.080
THANK YOU.

33:51.090 --> 33:54.680
SO, HOW YOU BEEN?

33:54.690 --> 33:55.950
I'M ON EDGE.

33:55.950 --> 33:57.680
I'M ANXIOUS.

33:57.690 --> 34:00.580
ABOUT?

34:00.590 --> 34:04.220
LOOK, COME ON,
YOU TAKING KELLY'S CASE?

34:04.220 --> 34:06.850
I'M GONNA DO IT.

34:06.850 --> 34:09.980
THANK YOU, LORD.

34:09.990 --> 34:11.180
COME ON, NAT.

34:11.190 --> 34:13.150
DON'T TAKE
THE LORD'S NAME IN VAIN.

34:13.150 --> 34:14.650
SORRY.

34:14.650 --> 34:17.050
NOW, YOU GUYS DO REALIZE
THIS IS GONNA BE TRICKY?

34:19.250 --> 34:20.450
WHY IS THAT?

34:20.450 --> 34:21.920
WELL, IN ORDER
FOR ME TO REP HER,

34:21.920 --> 34:25.880
I NEED TO BREAK CLIENT PRIVILEGE
WITH THE CAINS.

34:25.890 --> 34:28.420
OKAY.

34:28.420 --> 34:29.620
AND --
OKAY, I KNOW THAT.

34:29.620 --> 34:31.750
SO?

34:31.750 --> 34:35.680
I MEAN, YOU KNOW THAT LARRY
REPRESENTS THEM?

34:35.690 --> 34:36.880
ALL RIGHT, YEAH.
AND SO?

34:36.890 --> 34:39.120
WHAT DO WE --
WHAT DO WE DO?

34:39.120 --> 34:43.280
WELL, I GOT TO FIGURE OUT
A WAY AROUND IT.

34:43.290 --> 34:45.750
HOW DO WE DO THAT?

34:45.750 --> 34:47.350
YEAH, WELL,
THERE'S EVIDENCE OUT THERE

34:47.350 --> 34:49.220
THAT COULD HELP HER
SELF-DEFENSE CLAIM,

34:49.220 --> 34:51.480
BUT I CAN'T TELL YOU
WHERE IT IS.

34:51.490 --> 34:53.620
OH, COME ON.
IAN...

34:53.620 --> 34:54.750
MAN, LISTEN.
I CAN'T.

34:54.750 --> 34:57.050
LOOK, YOU GOT TO GIVE ME
SOMETHING.

34:57.050 --> 34:58.580
LOOK, YOU'LL KNOW
WHERE TO LOOK, MAN.

34:58.590 --> 35:00.950
YOU'RE A GOOD OFFICER.

35:00.950 --> 35:02.550
WOW.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

35:02.550 --> 35:04.280
RICK -- RICK...

35:04.290 --> 35:06.380
YEAH, HE ALSO WORKED
AT THE CHURCH.

35:06.390 --> 35:07.520
RICK?

35:07.520 --> 35:08.980
YEAH, ONE OF THE OFFICERS
AT THE STATION.

35:08.990 --> 35:11.850
HE'S TRYING TO GET
SOME INFORMATION.

35:11.850 --> 35:14.550
NOW -- NOW YOU'RE TALKING LIKE
THE OFFICER THAT I KNOW YOU ARE.

35:14.550 --> 35:15.720
YEAH.

35:15.720 --> 35:17.120
LAST TIME I TALKED TO HIM,
HE SAID THAT,

35:17.120 --> 35:20.820
UH, THERE WAS A CHAPLAIN
THAT WAS ALSO A MEMBER THERE

35:20.820 --> 35:24.750
AND POSSIBLY COULD BE
SOME MORE VICTIMS.

35:24.750 --> 35:26.020
OKAY, GOOD.
THAT'S WHAT YOU GOT TO DO.

35:26.020 --> 35:27.550
YOU GOT TO FIND
THE OTHERS.

35:27.550 --> 35:30.150
OKAY, SO LET'S SAY
WE FIND ALL THIS INFORMATION.

35:30.150 --> 35:31.550
AND THEN WHAT?
I MEAN, HOW ARE YOU GONNA

35:31.550 --> 35:35.650
REP HER
WORKING FOR LARRY?

35:35.650 --> 35:37.120
YEAH...

35:37.120 --> 35:38.850
REMEMBER THAT
PUBLIC DEFENDER KID?

35:38.850 --> 35:41.650
NOW, COME ON, IAN.
N-N-NOT THAT...

35:41.650 --> 35:43.220
PLEASE NOT THAT --
LISTEN, MAN.

35:43.220 --> 35:45.150
NOW, THAT KID DID WELL
IN SCHOOL.

35:45.150 --> 35:46.450
YEAH, BUT CAN HE ARGUE?

35:46.450 --> 35:48.120
HE'LL BE FINE.

35:48.120 --> 35:51.780
I'LL COACH HIM.

35:51.790 --> 35:54.320
NO.
I DON'T KNOW.

35:54.320 --> 35:56.420
I DON'T LIKE THIS, IAN.

35:56.420 --> 35:59.080
LISTEN, MAN,
THIS IS THE BEST I CAN DO.

35:59.090 --> 36:00.750
BUT THE OTHER PART OF IT IS
I DON'T EVEN THINK

36:00.750 --> 36:03.150
YOU'LL HAVE TO
GO TO COURT.

36:03.150 --> 36:04.750
HOW IS THAT?

36:04.750 --> 36:07.550
WELL, ONCE HE GETS
THE EVIDENCE, LAYS IT OUT

36:07.550 --> 36:11.150
IN FRONT OF THE D.A., SHE'LL
PROBABLY OFFER HER A DEAL.

36:11.150 --> 36:13.820
OH, NO, NO, NO.
SHE WON'T TAKE A DEAL.

36:13.820 --> 36:16.080
YEAH, KELLY WON'T.

36:16.090 --> 36:17.950
BUT THIS IS
AN ELECTION YEAR.

36:17.950 --> 36:19.620
SHE WON'T WANT TO
BE EMBARRASSED,

36:19.620 --> 36:21.580
ESPECIALLY IN FRONT
OF A PUBLIC DEFENDER.

36:24.050 --> 36:27.050
HMM.

36:27.050 --> 36:29.050
AND YOU REALLY THINK
THIS KID CAN DO IT?

36:29.050 --> 36:30.520
YEAH, HE'LL DO IT.

36:30.520 --> 36:32.380
IT'LL CHANGE
HIS CAREER OVERNIGHT.

36:34.320 --> 36:35.650
WELL...

36:35.650 --> 36:37.220
I GUESS I'M RUNNING OUT
OF OPTIONS.

36:37.220 --> 36:38.420
I GUESS WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO TRY THIS.

36:38.420 --> 36:39.480
GOOD.

36:39.490 --> 36:40.880
SO, I KNOW
YOU'LL GIVE HIM A CALL,

36:40.890 --> 36:43.250
BUT THE FIRST THING YOU GOT
TO DO IS FIND THAT EVIDENCE.

36:43.250 --> 36:45.520
WELL, IT'D BE NICE IF YOU
POINTED ME

36:45.520 --> 36:47.150
IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION.

36:49.620 --> 36:51.350
LISTEN, MAN.
I CAN'T.

36:51.350 --> 36:53.280
OH, COME ON, IAN.

36:53.290 --> 36:55.380
LISTEN.
IT'S CLOSE, ALL RIGHT?

36:55.390 --> 36:57.850
IT'S REAL CLOSE, MAN.
IT'S CLOSER THAN YOU THINK.

37:01.150 --> 37:02.280
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

37:02.290 --> 37:04.880
COME O--
COME ON IN.

37:04.890 --> 37:06.020
HI.
HEY.

37:06.020 --> 37:08.620
HEY.
HI, ALEX.

37:08.620 --> 37:10.220
SORRY, I JUST, UH --
JUST GOT A SITTER.

37:10.220 --> 37:11.820
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:11.820 --> 37:13.150
HEY.
HI, ALEX.

37:13.150 --> 37:15.080
THANKS FOR INVITING ME.

37:15.090 --> 37:17.780
THIS IS THE ATTORNEY
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.

37:17.790 --> 37:20.750
OH! HI.
HI.

37:20.750 --> 37:22.080
-YEAH, IAN, THIS IS AL--
-YEAH, JENNIFER.

37:22.090 --> 37:23.950
YEAH, WE'VE MET.

37:23.950 --> 37:27.420
Natalie: NO.

37:27.420 --> 37:29.480
THIS IS ALEX.

37:29.490 --> 37:33.620
ALEX?
NO, THIS IS JENNIFER.

37:33.620 --> 37:37.320
NO, I'M -- I'M ALEX.

37:37.320 --> 37:40.250
ALEX?

37:40.250 --> 37:42.080
OH, I'M SORRY, I...

37:42.090 --> 37:44.820
THOUGHT YOU WERE
SOMEONE ELSE.

37:44.820 --> 37:47.350
UH, OKAY.

37:47.350 --> 37:49.950
NO PROBLEM.
IT'S...

37:49.950 --> 37:51.750
I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO GET DINNER STARTED.

37:51.750 --> 37:53.150
WELL, CAN I AT LEAST
HELP YOU?

37:53.150 --> 37:54.820
I DIDN'T EVEN BRING ANYTHING
WITH ME. SORRY.

37:54.820 --> 37:56.620
YEAH, YEAH.

37:56.620 --> 37:58.420
UH, IAN.

37:58.420 --> 38:01.220
SHE WANTED TO KNOW IF YOU COULD
LOOK OVER HER DIVORCE PAPERS.

38:01.220 --> 38:02.320
NATALIE!
WHAT?

38:02.320 --> 38:03.820
I'M -- LOOK, I'M SORRY.
NO, NO, NO.

38:03.820 --> 38:05.220
IT'S JUST LOOKING
AT THE PAPERS.

38:05.220 --> 38:06.680
LADIES, IT'S OKAY.
NO, IT'S OKAY.

38:06.690 --> 38:07.750
NO, IT'S JUST
LOOKING OVER THEM.

38:07.750 --> 38:10.950
LISTEN. IT'S OKAY.
I'LL DO IT.

38:10.950 --> 38:12.620
REALLY?
YES.

38:12.620 --> 38:14.120
YOU REALLY DON'T MIND?

38:14.120 --> 38:17.420
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

38:17.420 --> 38:21.220
HE KIND OF WANTS THEM
BY TOMORROW.

38:21.220 --> 38:23.550
WHY THE RUSH?

38:23.550 --> 38:26.150
WELL, UH...

38:26.150 --> 38:29.480
IT'S A LONG STORY.

38:29.490 --> 38:32.820
WELL, I GUESS WE GOT
A LONG DINNER LOOKS LIKE.

38:32.820 --> 38:34.220
WELL, WE GOT PLENTY
OF WINE,

38:34.220 --> 38:37.320
SO YOU CAN FILL HIM IN,
JENNIFER.

38:39.720 --> 38:42.620
I'M SORRY.
I...

38:42.620 --> 38:44.350
YOU JUST REALLY
LOOK LIKE HER.

38:46.550 --> 38:49.080
WELL, I HOPE SHE WAS
A REALLY NICE LADY.

38:49.090 --> 38:50.280
YEAH, SHE WAS.

